description:
Building a cybersecurity capture the flag (CTF) platform tailored for the CyberStudents community and organization, which will include:
​
• dashboards for player, challenge, write-ups, and verification management;
• anti-cheat technology and moderation;
• learning content, resources, videos, and labs;
• connections with various backend APIs and Discord bots;
• donations with Stripe;
• DevOps and infrastructure tooling like Docker, Grafana, Prometheus, GitHub Actions, and PostHog; and
• marketing pages.
​
Uses the T3 stack (TypeScript, Next.js, Tailwind CSS, tRPC, Prisma w/ PostgreSQL).
​
NB: AI use was limited to GitHub Copilot for code completion; no files were primarily AI-generated.
